title: bingo_(game)
body:
A type of game in which players mark called numbers on printed cards and form certain patterns to win. There are two versions:

* In the American version of bingo, cards each have 24 (out of 75) numbers arranged on a 5x5 grid with the center square marked "free" and is considered filled. The 75 numbers have grouped into columns marked B, I, N, G, and O. An infinite number of winning patterns can be formed.

* In the British/European version of bingo (also known as Housie), cards each have 15 (out of 90) numbers arranged on a 9x3 grid, with the 12 haphazardly-placed, unoccupied blank spaces considered filled. Only three patterns can be considered as winning patterns: line, double line and "full house" (all numbers on the card filled).

Japanese refer "Bingo" (ビンゴ) to the American version and are more familiar with it.

She is very shy and distrusting towards other people - the reason for this is because of a troubled childhood that she had at an early age. The trauma of her upbringing weighs on her to this day. She cannot stand those who break their word, and literally tests the patience of those who try to get near her.

Her weapon, Geisterwand, allows her to summon a circular shield of maces to protect her, which, while primarily being usable for defensive purposes, can also be used as offense.

title: ah-64
body:
Assault [[helicopter]] in use by United States Army Aviation, the IDF and the JSDF, among others. Produced by Boeing. Recognition features include TADS/PNVS sensor assembly on nose, conventional wheeled landing gear, main-tail rotor configuration with four-bladed main rotor with swept tips. All-moving tailplane at end of low-mounted boom, along with a port-facing tail rotor with blades lying at angles of 60 and 120 degrees to each other. Engine pods on either side of the main fuselage. Crew of gunner and pilot under single canopy separated by bullet-resistant polycarbonate pane. Faired section at bottom of fuselage houses electronics.

Fixed armament of one 30mm M230 Chain Gun in underfuselage turret. The Apache's stub wings can carry various types of ordnance, including rockets, anti-tank missiles, and short-range air-to-air missiles.

The AH-64D Longbow variant has a flat radar dish mounted on top of the rotor mast.

title: hakamichi_shizune
body:
[[katawa_shoujo|Katawa Shoujo]] character.

Shizune is one of [[nakai hisao|Hisao's]] classmates, as well as the student council president who supervises every aspect of Yamaku's school festival. She has short dark blue hair and eyes, and wears glasses. She is deaf and mute, communicating primarily through sign language. Her friend [[mikado shiina|Misha]] is almost always at her side, translating everything Shizune signs and signing back to her, allowing for communication with other people. 

Shizune is strong-willed and very competitive.  Her favorite game is Risk and she even tries to be first to complete class assignments.

title: nao_(otosuki)
body:
The eldest son Nao is a bishounen/pretty boy whose appearance can be easily mistaken for a girl’s. Characterized by “his” (her?) long silky hair, Nao is a gentle and tidy person. His gentle demeanor and calming smile is said to attract many customers to the “Cherry Girls” cafe.

(Note: The term used to say he attracts customers was “kanbanmusume,” which implies a female that attracts male customers to the shop. In the original text, it said 看板娘 (?), since Nao is really a male.)

Nao wears a maid outfit which consists of a fascinating long sleeved kimono which lends itself to the shop’s name by being patterned with sakura flowers. The obi worn around his waist is also accented with an elegant sakura flower.

title: yuki_(otosuki)
body:
The second oldest son Yuki is strongly against dressing as a girl. Though he’s grown up opposing Nao’s femininity (which can be seen no matter which way you see him), he’s often mistaken as just putting on a “noble male” act (while dressing and looking like a girl). However, since helping the cafe is something that the entire family has decided not to go against, Yuki’s ended up having to “serve” in a maid outfit at the family’s cafe, “Cherry Girls.”

His maid costume consists of black and white colors in a gothic punk fashion. The black ribbon in his hair associates itself with the cafe’s namesake with a dark red blooming sakura flower. The skull accent supposedly gives off a sort of complex character vibe?

title: tomo_(otosuki)
body:
Tomo is the glasses wearing, cool and collected third son of the family and he gives off an intellectual vibe. Between the high tension of the other brothers, Tomo is the most composed and takes charge. However, he also has a sadistic side that comes and goes in that he likes to tease Yuki about his hate for dressing as a girl. Tomo handmakes all of the maid outfits for the sake of the Cherry Girls cafe, so perhaps he has a bit of a “tsundere” in him?

His maid outfit is mainly a pure white china dress. His headdress is decorated with scarlet sakura blossoms. His tight silhouette emphasized by his slender form is charming, and the high cut slit rather breathtaking!?

title: rio_(otosuki)
body:
Wearing his simple white tights, the fourth son Rio, together with the eldest Nao, are the two most popular “shounen” maids that attract customers to the Cherry Girls cafe. His simple-minded and charming behavior easily makes customers fall in love. If he knew about the kind of looks he was getting, would his service heat up?

His Alice in Wonderland inspired maid outfit fits his energetic personality perfectly. If he’s called as he runs around the cafe with his Cheshire cat knapsack, he’ll turn his head with a gentle flutter of his skirt. The boyish (?) silk hat with pink sakura just might be fitting for Rio.
